{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17612173","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17612173"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:19:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:19:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16267"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16267","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16267"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.61,0.29,0,0.03,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8958"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74618"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8958","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8958"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16267"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60112"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5247"},{"type":"tags","id":"7567"},{"type":"tags","id":"10114"},{"type":"tags","id":"10115"},{"type":"tags","id":"10676"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21304"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21307"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74618","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74618"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EPuberty involves complex hormonal changes that lead to sexual maturation. These changes are regulated by interactions between the hypothalamus, pituitary, and gonads.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a normal physiological change during puberty?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Development of diurnal rhythm in luteinising hormone and follicle-stimulating hormone secretion","Testosterone increases sex hormone-binding globulin production","Oestrogen decreases sex hormone-binding globulin production","Continuous gonadotrophin-releasing hormone secretion","Decreased sensitivity of gonadotrophs to gonadotrophin-releasing hormone"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring normal puberty, \u003Cstrong\u003Edevelopment of diurnal rhythm in luteinising hormone (LH) and follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) secretion\u003C/strong\u003E occurs, with peak levels during sleep. This pulsatile pattern is crucial for normal sexual development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETestosterone increases sex hormone-binding globulin production\u003C/strong\u003E - Testosterone actually decreases sex hormone-binding globulin (SHBG) production\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOestrogen decreases sex hormone-binding globulin production\u003C/strong\u003E - Oestrogen increases SHBG production\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContinuous gonadotrophin-releasing hormone secretion\u003C/strong\u003E - GnRH secretion becomes pulsatile, not continuous, during puberty\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased sensitivity of gonadotrophs to gonadotrophin-releasing hormone\u003C/strong\u003E - Sensitivity actually increases during puberty\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe establishment of pulsatile gonadotrophin-releasing hormone secretion and subsequent diurnal rhythm of LH and FSH are hallmark features of normal pubertal development.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Puberty normally begins between ages 8-13 in females and 9-14 in males, triggered by pulsatile gonadotrophin-releasing hormone secretion.","During puberty, luteinising hormone and follicle-stimulating hormone show a diurnal rhythm with peak secretion during sleep.","Sex hormone-binding globulin levels are regulated differently by sex hormones - testosterone decreases while oestrogen increases SHBG."],"references":["Howard SR. Interpretation of reproductive hormones before, during and after the pubertal transition-Identifying health and disordered puberty. Clin Endocrinol (Oxf). 2021 Nov;95(5):702-715. doi: 10.1111/cen.14578. Epub 2021 Aug 8. PMID: 34368982; PMCID: PMC9291332.","Rosenfield RL, Bordini B, Yu C. Comparison of detection of normal puberty in girls by a hormonal sleep test and a gonadotropin-releasing hormone agonist test. J Clin Endocrinol Metab. 2013 Apr;98(4):1591-601. doi: 10.1210/jc.2012-4136. Epub 2013 Mar 1. PMID: 23457407; PMCID: PMC3615202.","Lissauer, T., \u0026 Carroll, W. (Eds.). (2021). Illustrated Textbook of Paediatrics E-Book: Illustrated Textbook of Paediatrics E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60112"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16267"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60112","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60112"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T22:18:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-25T22:57:55+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8958"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74618"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"htt